Sweetie.

994
01:27:38,511 --> 01:27:42,181
You haven't coughed.
Not since I've been back.

995
01:27:42,349 --> 01:27:44,266
- Yeah.
- Have you told her yet?

996
01:27:45,227 --> 01:27:46,227
No.

997
01:27:46,394 --> 01:27:50,231
- You're gonna have to.
- I know.

998
01:27:51,566 --> 01:27:55,527
- Just tell her you love her.
- She knows.

999
01:27:56,821 --> 01:27:59,031
She needs to hear it from you.

1000
01:28:00,617 --> 01:28:03,118
Of course I love her.
I mean, I love her the same way...

1001
01:28:05,538 --> 01:28:07,164
...the same way I love you.

1002
01:29:00,385 --> 01:29:01,468
Good morning.

1003
01:29:01,803 --> 01:29:03,012
Oh, God.

1004
01:29:04,431 --> 01:29:07,683
- You're not on the couch.
- No, Tina, I'm not on the couch.

1005
01:29:07,851 --> 01:29:09,476
I mean, what's wrong with that?

1006
01:29:11,895 --> 01:29:13,187
What happens when you're gone?

1007
01:29:22,031 --> 01:29:23,072
Yeah?

1008
01:29:23,240 --> 01:29:25,408
The Albino is staying
at the Grand Hotel.

1009
01:29:27,911 --> 01:29:28,995
All right.

1010
01:29:33,500 --> 01:29:37,754
Hey. I'm not going anywhere.

1011
01:30:19,046 --> 01:30:21,047
- Hello.
- You spotted me.

1012
01:30:21,215 --> 01:30:24,175
- I'd have to be blind not to.
- Don't do anything stupid, Mitat.

1013
01:30:24,343 --> 01:30:26,219
Your girls are expecting you
home tonight.

1014
01:30:26,386 --> 01:30:28,554
So is your beautiful wife.

1015
01:30:30,766 --> 01:30:32,433
Who were you talking to?

1016
01:30:52,579 --> 01:30:53,621
Come on, accelerate!

1017
01:30:59,962 --> 01:31:01,045
Come on!

1018
01:31:18,105 --> 01:31:19,355
Come on, faster!

1019
01:32:28,258 --> 01:32:29,508
Have we lost him?

1020
01:32:36,808 --> 01:32:38,851
This kind of guy,
he'd never give up.

1021
01:33:15,806 --> 01:33:17,473
Why you don't kill me already?

1022
01:33:19,685 --> 01:33:22,728
Because you're the father who knows best.

1023
01:35:32,275 --> 01:35:33,567
Just kill him!

1024
01:36:01,930 --> 01:36:02,930
Vivi...

1025
01:36:42,554 --> 01:36:43,929
Welcome back.

1026
01:36:56,860 --> 01:36:59,028
You let the Wolf
slip through your hands again.

1027
01:37:00,530 --> 01:37:01,572
Where am I?

1028
01:37:02,532 --> 01:37:03,866
A safe place.

1029
01:37:06,738 --> 01:37:09,239
We got your lab results
back today, Ethan.

1030
01:37:09,407 --> 01:37:13,076
I was actually pretty curious myself.
And as it turns out,

1031
01:37:13,244 --> 01:37:16,288
it looks like the treatment's
having a positive effect on you.

1032
01:37:18,458 --> 01:37:22,669
I don't want to spend the rest of my life
killing for you, Vivi.

1033
01:37:22,837 --> 01:37:24,629
You're almost there, Ethan.

1034
01:37:26,841 --> 01:37:28,175
Kill the Wolf.

1035
01:37:31,053 --> 01:37:32,971
I'm gonna need a new suit.

1036
01:37:35,674 --> 01:37:37,342
You heard him.

1037
01:37:44,308 --> 01:37:48,228
There has been a change in plans.
We're leaving tonight.

1038
01:37:48,395 --> 01:37:50,897
Take me to my partner's house.

1039
01:37:51,065 --> 01:37:53,233
He will help me to get out of Paris.

1040
01:37:56,237 --> 01:37:59,072
- Mom, don't ruin my night.
- Why don't you try them on?

1041
01:37:59,240 --> 01:38:01,115
No!

1042
01:38:02,409 --> 01:38:04,994
- Listen, just at least try them on?
- No!

1043
01:38:13,629 --> 01:38:14,629
Whoa!

1044
01:38:19,176 --> 01:38:21,886
Just smile and have fun.

1045
01:38:22,054 --> 01:38:25,557
Why? I hate these shoes.
I look like Little Miss Sunshine.

1046
01:38:31,981 --> 01:38:33,815
- You look great, honey.
- No, I don't.

1047
01:38:44,034 --> 01:38:46,369
- Zoe.
- Hugh.

1048
01:38:46,537 --> 01:38:48,580
- You look great.
- Really, I do?

1049
01:38:48,747 --> 01:38:49,789
Yeah, of course.

1050
01:38:52,459 --> 01:38:55,086
Oh, Mr. Renner, Mrs. Renner,

1051
01:38:55,569 --> 01:38:56,778
these are my parents.

1052
01:38:56,946 --> 01:38:58,905
Nice to see you again.
Thanks for inviting us.

1053
01:38:59,073 --> 01:39:00,573
You're welcome.

1054
01:39:00,741 --> 01:39:02,617
This is Ethan, Zooey's dad.

1055
01:39:02,785 --> 01:39:04,786
Hi. And this is my partner.

1056
01:39:09,250 --> 01:39:10,750
Pleasure to meet you.

1057
01:39:13,629 --> 01:39:14,796
And you.

1058
01:39:21,804 --> 01:39:22,804
How do you do?

1059
01:39:25,140 --> 01:39:26,140
Enchanté.

1060
01:39:30,104 --> 01:39:31,271
Wow.

1061
01:39:42,032 --> 01:39:43,408
Wow.

1062
01:39:44,952 --> 01:39:46,619
- May I take this? Thank you, sir.
- Yeah.

1063
01:39:59,675 --> 01:40:01,301
Isn't this great?

1064
01:40:01,468 --> 01:40:02,593
Yeah.

1065
01:40:04,471 --> 01:40:06,097
Zooey, do me a favor.

1066
01:40:07,266 --> 01:40:09,475
Try and use your best
judgment with Hugh tonight.

1067
01:40:19,737 --> 01:40:20,737
Cheers.

1068
01:40:35,210 --> 01:40:36,627
You're working again!

1069
01:40:38,505 --> 01:40:41,507
Yeah. There's a problem here.

1070
01:40:43,635 --> 01:40:46,387
That's why you came back to Paris?

1071
01:40:46,555 --> 01:40:49,849
No. I came back to see you and Zooey.

1072
01:40:50,017 --> 01:40:51,642
It was all a lie.

1073
01:40:51,810 --> 01:40:54,103
You promised you'd keep
your work away from us.

1074
01:40:54,271 --> 01:40:57,315
- You're probably not even sick.
- It's not a lie, Tina.

1075
01:40:57,483 --> 01:40:59,650
Right now I don't
have the time to explain.

1076
01:41:22,800 --> 01:41:24,509
The police will be here
in ten minutes.

1077
01:41:27,137 --> 01:41:29,305
- You used us both!
- No, I would never do that.

1078
01:41:29,473 --> 01:41:31,349
Make sure the street's blocked.

1079
01:41:32,893 --> 01:41:35,019
At least have the decency
to look at me.

1080
01:41:45,322 --> 01:41:46,489
Kill him.

1081
01:41:48,367 --> 01:41:49,367
It's just bad luck.

1082
01:41:58,794 --> 01:42:01,712
Wow, this is unbelievable.

1083
01:42:01,880 --> 01:42:03,965
Yeah. I know. It's crazy.

1084
01:42:14,059 --> 01:42:15,476
I'm gonna be sick.

1085
01:42:16,478 --> 01:42:18,062
Come with me.

1086
01:42:37,082 --> 01:42:38,541
No, please don't go.
Come home with me.

1087
01:42:38,709 --> 01:42:40,710
Just please stay here.

1088
01:42:54,845 --> 01:42:56,054
- Zooey!
- What?

1089
01:42:56,222 --> 01:42:57,347
Get down!

1090
01:43:28,045 --> 01:43:29,629
You hear me in there?

1091
01:43:30,923 --> 01:43:32,465
I'm sending you down.

1092
01:44:44,535 --> 01:44:45,952
Oh, shit.

1093
01:45:04,263 --> 01:45:05,263
Don't!

1094
01:45:05,431 --> 01:45:06,931
You never give up, huh?

1095
01:45:09,643 --> 01:45:10,935
Yes.

1096
01:45:12,646 --> 01:45:14,439
I gotta...

1097
01:45:36,921 --> 01:45:38,713
Oh, my God.

1098
01:45:40,841 --> 01:45:42,550
Am I in hell?

1099
01:45:42,718 --> 01:45:45,553
So that's what it looks like
to you, Ethan.

1100
01:45:45,721 --> 01:45:48,890
Figures.

1101
01:45:50,726 --> 01:45:52,810
- Finish it.
- What?

1102
01:45:55,272 --> 01:45:58,316
Jesus Christ!

1103
01:46:04,907 --> 01:46:06,908
Promise me.
Are you really done working for them?

1104
01:46:08,244 --> 01:46:09,494
- Ethan!
- Ethan.

1105
01:46:09,662 --> 01:46:10,870
It was all a lie.

1106
01:46:11,038 --> 01:46:12,997
Ethan!
Promise you'll never lie to me again.

1107
01:46:13,165 --> 01:46:16,042
Are you really done working for them?
Promise me.

1108
01:46:16,210 --> 01:46:18,211
Finish it.

1109
01:46:19,171 --> 01:46:21,047
I don't think so.

1110
01:46:21,840 --> 01:46:25,760
The wife wants me to give it up.

1111
01:47:00,129 --> 01:47:01,379
Can I talk to her?

1112
01:47:01,547 --> 01:47:04,340
No, she's down on the beach
right now throwing rocks.

1113
01:47:04,508 --> 01:47:06,884
- What?
- Yeah, we're...

1114
01:47:07,052 --> 01:47:08,720
We're taking a break
from each other right now.

1115
01:47:08,887 --> 01:47:10,930
At least she's not throwing them at me.

1116
01:47:11,098 --> 01:47:13,182
Is everything all right?

1117
01:47:13,350 --> 01:47:17,437
Yeah, it's been all right.
There's been good and bad days.

1118
01:47:17,604 --> 01:47:19,689
She said things, I've said things.

1119
01:47:19,857 --> 01:47:22,275
There's been some tears,

1120
01:47:22,443 --> 01:47:24,485
but the week overall's
been really worth it.

1121
01:47:58,020 --> 01:47:59,020
Hey.

1122
01:48:00,481 --> 01:48:02,690
These are some presents
from me and, um...

1123
01:48:02,858 --> 01:48:05,026
...a package that was
dropped at the house.

1124
01:48:05,194 --> 01:48:08,071
I can hear your car running.
Are you gonna go back?

1125
01:48:14,036 --> 01:48:15,787
I love you, Tina.

1126
01:48:18,916 --> 01:48:24,337
If I could say one word to you
to change your mind,

1127
01:48:24,505 --> 01:48:25,922
would you give me that chance?

1128
01:48:27,841 --> 01:48:29,133
I've...

1129
01:48:29,301 --> 01:48:32,095
I've bungled my whole life, Tina.
I've...

1130
01:48:32,262 --> 01:48:35,556
I've been a terrible husband,
I've done...

1131
01:48:35,724 --> 01:48:38,351
I've done stuff that's
impossible to explain.

1132
01:48:38,519 --> 01:48:43,231
And now I'm about to spend the rest of
my life, whatever I have left, missing you.

1133
01:48:45,109 --> 01:48:50,071
I just wanna hang out as long as I can
with my daughter and my wife.

1134
01:48:53,951 --> 01:48:56,744
- What's the word?
- What?

1135
01:48:56,912 --> 01:48:58,413
What's the one word
to make me change my mind?

1136
01:48:58,580 --> 01:49:02,667
It's, uh... it's Christmas.

1137
01:49:05,539 --> 01:49:07,248
That's two, Ethan.

1138
01:49:07,416 --> 01:49:09,709
- Hey, Mom!
- Hi, sweetie.

1139
01:49:09,877 --> 01:49:11,086
I'm so glad you came!

1140
01:49:14,590 --> 01:49:16,091
Come on, let's go inside.

1141
01:49:17,218 --> 01:49:18,927
Dad's gonna make us hot cocoa.

1142
01:49:23,849 --> 01:49:24,933
Come on.

1143
01:49:46,122 --> 01:49:47,539
Is Dad a badass?

1144
01:49:49,542 --> 01:49:53,378
Well, he's, um...
He's done some things.

1145
01:49:58,926 --> 01:50:02,345
You think Dad's gonna stick around?

1146
01:50:02,513 --> 01:50:04,013
As long as he can, sweetheart.

1147
01:50:06,517 --> 01:50:08,143
He loves you so much.

1148
01:50:38,132 --> 01:50:39,132
TCS Subtitling

